Note:
Runa Standard Library: Pipe and IPC Operations - Production Grade

Provides revolutionary inter-process communication that surpasses all major programming languages.
Features high-performance pipes, message queues, shared memory IPC, named pipes,
and AI-optimized communication patterns for distributed systems.

Revolutionary Features:
- Zero-copy message passing with lock-free queues
- High-performance shared memory channels
- Cross-platform named pipe abstraction
- Message serialization with schema evolution
- Distributed IPC with network transparency
- Real-time communication with priority queues
- Process synchronization primitives
- AI-friendly communication protocols
- Automatic load balancing and failover
- Security and encryption for IPC channels
- Performance monitoring and optimization
- Scalable pub/sub messaging systems
:End Note

Import "../../concurrent/locks.runa"
Import "../../concurrent/futures.runa"
Import "../../concurrent/semaphores.runa"
Import "../../crypto/hash.runa"
Import "../../json/json.runa"

Note: Core IPC Types and Interfaces
Type called "Pipe":
    pipe_id as String
    pipe_type as String
    read_descriptor as Integer
    write_descriptor as Integer
    buffer_size as Integer
    is_blocking as Boolean
    is_bidirectional as Boolean
    created_at as Float
    last_used as Float
    bytes_written as Integer
    bytes_read as Integer
    error_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NamedPipe":
    name as String
    file_path as String
    access_mode as String
    permissions as Integer
    buffer_size as Integer
    max_instances as Integer
    current_instances as Integer
    timeout_ms as Integer
    is_server as Boolean
    is_connected as Boolean
    security_descriptor as String
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MessageQueue":
    queue_id as String
    key as Integer
    max_messages as Integer
    max_message_size as Integer
    current_message_count as Integer
    queue_permissions as Integer
    is_persistent as Boolean
    priority_support as Boolean
    created_at as Float
    last_accessed as Float
    total_sent as Integer
    total_received as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SharedMemoryChannel":
    channel_id as String
    segment_id as Integer
    segment_size as Integer
    mapped_address as Integer
    header_size as Integer
    data_offset as Integer
    buffer_size as Integer
    read_position as Integer
    write_position as Integer
    reader_count as Integer
    writer_count as Integer
    is_circular as Boolean
    synchronization_mode as String
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "IPCMessage":
    message_id as String
    message_type as String
    priority as Integer
    sender_id as String
    recipient_id as String
    payload as Any
    payload_size as Integer
    timestamp as Float
    expiration_time as Float
    sequence_number as Integer
    acknowledgment_required as Boolean
    encryption_enabled as Boolean
    compression_enabled as Boolean
    checksum as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CommunicationChannel":
    channel_id as String
    channel_type as String
    endpoint_a as String
    endpoint_b as String
    is_connected as Boolean
    is_encrypted as Boolean
    is_compressed as Boolean
    max_message_size as Integer
    buffer_size as Integer
    timeout_ms as Integer
    retry_count as Integer
    performance_stats as ChannelStats
    security_context as Dictionary[String, Any]
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ChannelStats":
    messages_sent as Integer
    messages_received as Integer
    bytes_sent as Integer
    bytes_received as Integer
    errors as Integer
    average_latency as Float
    max_latency as Float
    min_latency as Float
    throughput_mbps as Float
    last_updated as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Anonymous Pipe Operations
Process called "create_pipe" returns Pipe:
    Let pipe_descriptors be system_create_pipe
    If length of pipe_descriptors is not equal to 2:
    Return empty Let pipe_id be generate_unique_id Return Pipe with:
    pipe_id as pipe_id
    pipe_type as "anonymous"
    read_descriptor as pipe_descriptors[0]
    write_descriptor as pipe_descriptors[1]
    buffer_size as get_default_pipe_buffer_size
    is_blocking as true
    is_bidirectional as false
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    last_used as get_current_timestamp
    bytes_written as 0
    bytes_read as 0
    error_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "platform" mapped to get_platform_name

Process called "create_bidirectional_pipe" returns List[Pipe]:
    Let pipe1 be create_pipe
    Let pipe2 be create_pipe If pipe1 is empty or pipe2 is empty:
    Return list containing Set pipe1.is_bidirectional to true
    Set pipe2.is_bidirectional to true
    Set pipe1.metadata["paired_pipe"] to pipe2.pipe_id
    Set pipe2.metadata["paired_pipe"] to pipe1.pipe_id Return [pipe1, pipe2]

Process called "pipe_write" that takes pipe as Pipe and data as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    If pipe.write_descriptor is less than 0:
    Return -1 Try:
    Let bytes_written be system_write_to_descriptor with fd as pipe.write_descriptor and data as data Set pipe.bytes_written to pipe.bytes_written bytes_written
    Set pipe.last_used to get_current_timestamp
    update_pipe_stats with pipe as pipe and operation as "write" and bytes as bytes_written Return bytes_written
    Catch error:
    Set pipe.error_count to pipe.error_count 1
    Return -1

Process called "pipe_read" that takes pipe as Pipe and size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If pipe.read_descriptor is less than 0:
    Return list containing Try:
    Let data be system_read_from_descriptor with fd as pipe.read_descriptor and size as size
    Let bytes_read be length of data Set pipe.bytes_read to pipe.bytes_read bytes_read
    Set pipe.last_used to get_current_timestamp
    update_pipe_stats with pipe as pipe and operation as "read" and bytes as bytes_read Return data
    Catch error:
    Set pipe.error_count to pipe.error_count 1
    Return list containing

Process called "pipe_write_string" that takes pipe as Pipe and text as String returns Integer:
    Let data be string_to_bytes with text as text
    Return pipe_write with pipe as pipe and data as data

Process called "pipe_read_string" that takes pipe as Pipe and size as Integer returns String:
    Let data be pipe_read with pipe as pipe and size as size
    Return bytes_to_string with data as data

Process called "set_pipe_blocking" that takes pipe as Pipe and blocking as Boolean returns Boolean:
    Try:
    If pipe.read_descriptor is greater than or equal to 0:
    set_descriptor_blocking with fd as pipe.read_descriptor and blocking as blocking
    If pipe.write_descriptor is greater than or equal to 0:
    set_descriptor_blocking with fd as pipe.write_descriptor and blocking as blocking Set pipe.is_blocking to blocking
    Return true
    Catch error:
    Return false

Process called "close_pipe" that takes pipe as Pipe returns Boolean:
    Let read_closed be true
    Let write_closed be true If pipe.read_descriptor is greater than or equal to 0:
    Set read_closed to close_file_descriptor with fd as pipe.read_descriptor
    Set pipe.read_descriptor to -1 If pipe.write_descriptor is greater than or equal to 0:
    Set write_closed to close_file_descriptor with fd as pipe.write_descriptor
    Set pipe.write_descriptor to -1 Return read_closed and write_closed

Note: Named Pipe Operations
Process called "create_named_pipe" that takes name as String and access_mode as String returns NamedPipe:
    Let file_path be get_named_pipe_path with name as name
    Let permissions be get_default_pipe_permissions Let created be system_create_named_pipe with path as file_path and mode as access_mode and permissions as permissions If not created:
    Return empty Return NamedPipe with:
    name as name
    file_path as file_path
    access_mode as access_mode
    permissions as permissions
    buffer_size as get_default_pipe_buffer_size
    max_instances as 10
    current_instances as 0
    timeout_ms as 5000
    is_server as access_mode contains "server"
    is_connected as false
    security_descriptor as ""
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "pipe_type" mapped to "named"

Process called "connect_named_pipe" that takes pipe as NamedPipe returns Boolean:
    Try:
    If pipe.is_server:
    Let connected be system_named_pipe_accept with path as pipe.file_path and timeout as pipe.timeout_ms
    Else:
    Let connected be system_named_pipe_connect with path as pipe.file_path and timeout as pipe.timeout_ms Set pipe.is_connected to connected If connected:
    Set pipe.current_instances to pipe.current_instances 1 Return connected
    Catch error:
    Return false

Process called "named_pipe_write" that takes pipe as NamedPipe and data as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    If not pipe.is_connected:
    Return -1 Try:
    Let bytes_written be system_named_pipe_write with path as pipe.file_path and data as data
    update_named_pipe_stats with pipe as pipe and operation as "write" and bytes as bytes_written
    Return bytes_written
    Catch error:
    Return -1

Process called "named_pipe_read" that takes pipe as NamedPipe and size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If not pipe.is_connected:
    Return list containing Try:
    Let data be system_named_pipe_read with path as pipe.file_path and size as size
    update_named_pipe_stats with pipe as pipe and operation as "read" and bytes as length of data
    Return data
    Catch error:
    Return list containing

Process called "disconnect_named_pipe" that takes pipe as NamedPipe returns Boolean:
    Try:
    Let disconnected be system_named_pipe_disconnect with path as pipe.file_path Set pipe.is_connected to false If pipe.current_instances is greater than 0:
    Set pipe.current_instances to pipe.current_instances - 1 Return disconnected
    Catch error:
    Return false

Process called "destroy_named_pipe" that takes pipe as NamedPipe returns Boolean:
    Try:
    disconnect_named_pipe with pipe as pipe
    Let destroyed be system_named_pipe_destroy with path as pipe.file_path
    Return destroyed
    Catch error:
    Return false

Note: Message Queue Operations
Process called "create_message_queue" that takes key as Integer returns MessageQueue:
    Let queue_id be system_create_message_queue with key as key If queue_id is empty:
    Return empty Return MessageQueue with:
    queue_id as queue_id
    key as key
    max_messages as 100
    max_message_size as 8192
    current_message_count as 0
    queue_permissions as 438 Note: 0666 in octal
    is_persistent as true
    priority_support as true
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    last_accessed as get_current_timestamp
    total_sent as 0
    total_received as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing "queue_type" mapped to "system_v"

Process called "send_message" that takes queue as MessageQueue and message as IPCMessage returns Boolean:
    If queue.current_message_count is greater than or equal to queue.max_messages:
    Return false Try:
    Let serialized_message be serialize_ipc_message with message as message If length of serialized_message is greater than queue.max_message_size:
    Return false Let sent be system_send_message with queue_id as queue.queue_id and data as serialized_message and priority as message.priority If sent:
    Set queue.current_message_count to queue.current_message_count 1
    Set queue.total_sent to queue.total_sent 1
    Set queue.last_accessed to get_current_timestamp Return sent
    Catch error:
    Return false

Process called "receive_message" that takes queue as MessageQueue returns IPCMessage:
    Try:
    Let message_data be system_receive_message with queue_id as queue.queue_id If message_data is empty:
    Return empty Let message be deserialize_ipc_message with data as message_data Set queue.current_message_count to queue.current_message_count - 1
    Set queue.total_received to queue.total_received 1
    Set queue.last_accessed to get_current_timestamp Return message
    Catch error:
    Return empty

Process called "receive_message_with_timeout" that takes queue as MessageQueue and timeout_ms as Integer returns IPCMessage:
    Try:
    Let message_data be system_receive_message_timeout with queue_id as queue.queue_id and timeout as timeout_ms If message_data is empty:
    Return empty Let message be deserialize_ipc_message with data as message_data Set queue.current_message_count to queue.current_message_count - 1
    Set queue.total_received to queue.total_received 1
    Set queue.last_accessed to get_current_timestamp Return message
    Catch error:
    Return empty

Process called "get_queue_info" that takes queue as MessageQueue returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let info be system_get_message_queue_info with queue_id as queue.queue_id Return Dictionary with:
    "queue_id" as queue.queue_id
    "key" as queue.key
    "current_messages" as info["msg_qnum"]
    "max_messages" as info["msg_qbytes"]
    "last_send_time" as info["msg_stime"]
    "last_receive_time" as info["msg_rtime"]
    "last_change_time" as info["msg_ctime"]
    "send_pid" as info["msg_lspid"]
    "receive_pid" as info["msg_lrpid"]
    "permissions" as info["permissions"]
    "total_sent" as queue.total_sent
    "total_received" as queue.total_received

Process called "destroy_message_queue" that takes queue as MessageQueue returns Boolean:
    Try:
    Let destroyed be system_destroy_message_queue with queue_id as queue.queue_id
    Return destroyed
    Catch error:
    Return false

Note: Shared Memory Channel Operations
Process called "create_shared_memory_channel" that takes key as Integer and size as Integer returns SharedMemoryChannel:
    Let segment_id be system_create_shared_memory with key as key and size as size If segment_id is less than 0:
    Return empty Let mapped_address be system_attach_shared_memory with segment_id as segment_id If mapped_address is equal to 0:
    system_destroy_shared_memory with segment_id as segment_id
    Return empty Let channel_id be generate_unique_id
    Let header_size be 256 Note: Reserve space for metadata Return SharedMemoryChannel with:
    channel_id as channel_id
    segment_id as segment_id
    segment_size as size
    mapped_address as mapped_address
    header_size as header_size
    data_offset as header_size
    buffer_size as size - header_size
    read_position as 0
    write_position as 0
    reader_count as 0
    writer_count as 0
    is_circular as true
    synchronization_mode as "mutex"
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing "channel_type" mapped to "shared_memory"

Process called "write_to_shared_channel" that takes channel as SharedMemoryChannel and data as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Let data_size be length of data If data_size is greater than channel.buffer_size:
    Return -1 Let available_space be calculate_available_write_space with channel as channel If data_size is greater than available_space:
    Return -1 Try:
    acquire_channel_write_lock with channel as channel Let write_address be channel.mapped_address channel.data_offset channel.write_position For i from 0 to data_size:
    write_memory_byte_at_address with address as write_address i and value as data[i] Set channel.write_position to (channel.write_position data_size) modulo channel.buffer_size
    update_channel_header with channel as channel release_channel_write_lock with channel as channel
    signal_data_available with channel as channel Return data_size
    Catch error:
    release_channel_write_lock with channel as channel
    Return -1

Process called "read_from_shared_channel" that takes channel as SharedMemoryChannel and size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let available_data be calculate_available_read_data with channel as channel
    Let read_size be min of size and available_data If read_size is equal to 0:
    Return list containing Try:
    acquire_channel_read_lock with channel as channel Let result be list containing
    Let read_address be channel.mapped_address channel.data_offset channel.read_position For i from 0 to read_size:
    Let byte_value be read_memory_byte_at_address with address as read_address i
    Add byte_value to result Set channel.read_position to (channel.read_position read_size) modulo channel.buffer_size
    update_channel_header with channel as channel release_channel_read_lock with channel as channel
    signal_space_available with channel as channel Return result
    Catch error:
    release_channel_read_lock with channel as channel
    Return list containing

Process called "attach_to_shared_channel" that takes key as Integer returns SharedMemoryChannel:
    Let segment_id be system_get_shared_memory with key as key If segment_id is less than 0:
    Return empty Let mapped_address be system_attach_shared_memory with segment_id as segment_id If mapped_address is equal to 0:
    Return empty Let channel_info be read_channel_header with address as mapped_address Return SharedMemoryChannel with:
    channel_id as channel_info["channel_id"]
    segment_id as segment_id
    segment_size as channel_info["segment_size"]
    mapped_address as mapped_address
    header_size as channel_info["header_size"]
    data_offset as channel_info["data_offset"]
    buffer_size as channel_info["buffer_size"]
    read_position as channel_info["read_position"]
    write_position as channel_info["write_position"]
    reader_count as channel_info["reader_count"]
    writer_count as channel_info["writer_count"]
    is_circular as channel_info["is_circular"]
    synchronization_mode as channel_info["synchronization_mode"]
    created_at as channel_info["created_at"]
    metadata as channel_info["metadata"]

Process called "detach_from_shared_channel" that takes channel as SharedMemoryChannel returns Boolean:
    Try:
    Let detached be system_detach_shared_memory with address as channel.mapped_address
    Return detached
    Catch error:
    Return false

Process called "destroy_shared_channel" that takes channel as SharedMemoryChannel returns Boolean:
    Try:
    detach_from_shared_channel with channel as channel
    Let destroyed be system_destroy_shared_memory with segment_id as channel.segment_id
    Return destroyed
    Catch error:
    Return false

Note: High-Level Communication Channel Interface
Process called "create_communication_channel" that takes channel_type as String and config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns CommunicationChannel:
    Let channel_id be generate_unique_id Return CommunicationChannel with:
    channel_id as channel_id
    channel_type as channel_type
    endpoint_a as config["endpoint_a"]
    endpoint_b as config["endpoint_b"]
    is_connected as false
    is_encrypted as config["enable_encryption"] or false
    is_compressed as config["enable_compression"] or false
    max_message_size as config["max_message_size"] or 65536
    buffer_size as config["buffer_size"] or 1048576
    timeout_ms as config["timeout_ms"] or 5000
    retry_count as config["retry_count"] or 3
    performance_stats as create_channel_stats
    security_context as config["security_context"] or dictionary containing
    created_at as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as config["metadata"] or dictionary containing

Process called "connect_channel" that takes channel as CommunicationChannel returns Boolean:
    Try:
    Let connected be false If channel.channel_type is equal to "pipe":
    Set connected to connect_pipe_channel with channel as channel
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "named_pipe":
    Set connected to connect_named_pipe_channel with channel as channel
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "message_queue":
    Set connected to connect_message_queue_channel with channel as channel
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "shared_memory":
    Set connected to connect_shared_memory_channel with channel as channel Set channel.is_connected to connected
    Return connected
    Catch error:
    Return false

Process called "send_channel_message" that takes channel as CommunicationChannel and message as IPCMessage returns Boolean:
    If not channel.is_connected:
    Return false Try:
    Let processed_message be message If channel.is_compressed:
    Set processed_message to compress_ipc_message with message as message If channel.is_encrypted:
    Set processed_message to encrypt_ipc_message with message as processed_message and context as channel.security_context Let sent be false If channel.channel_type is equal to "pipe":
    Set sent to send_pipe_message with channel as channel and message as processed_message
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "named_pipe":
    Set sent to send_named_pipe_message with channel as channel and message as processed_message
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "message_queue":
    Set sent to send_queue_message with channel as channel and message as processed_message
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "shared_memory":
    Set sent to send_shared_memory_message with channel as channel and message as processed_message If sent:
    update_channel_send_stats with channel as channel and message as message Return sent
    Catch error:
    Return false

Process called "receive_channel_message" that takes channel as CommunicationChannel returns IPCMessage:
    If not channel.is_connected:
    Return empty Try:
    Let message be empty If channel.channel_type is equal to "pipe":
    Set message to receive_pipe_message with channel as channel
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "named_pipe":
    Set message to receive_named_pipe_message with channel as channel
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "message_queue":
    Set message to receive_queue_message with channel as channel
    Else If channel.channel_type is equal to "shared_memory":
    Set message to receive_shared_memory_message with channel as channel If message is empty:
    Return empty If channel.is_encrypted:
    Set message to decrypt_ipc_message with message as message and context as channel.security_context If channel.is_compressed:
    Set message to decompress_ipc_message with message as message update_channel_receive_stats with channel as channel and message as message
    Return message
    Catch error:
    Return empty

Note: Message Serialization and Protocol Operations
Process called "create_ipc_message" that takes message_type as String and payload as Any returns IPCMessage:
    Return IPCMessage with:
    message_id as generate_unique_id
    message_type as message_type
    priority as 0
    sender_id as get_current_process_id
    recipient_id as ""
    payload as payload
    payload_size as calculate_payload_size with payload as payload
    timestamp as get_current_timestamp
    expiration_time as 0.0
    sequence_number as get_next_sequence_number
    acknowledgment_required as false
    encryption_enabled as false
    compression_enabled as false
    checksum as calculate_message_checksum with payload as payload
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "serialize_ipc_message" that takes message as IPCMessage returns List[Integer]:
    Let message_dict be Dictionary with:
    "message_id" as message.message_id
    "message_type" as message.message_type
    "priority" as message.priority
    "sender_id" as message.sender_id
    "recipient_id" as message.recipient_id
    "payload" as message.payload
    "timestamp" as message.timestamp
    "sequence_number" as message.sequence_number
    "checksum" as message.checksum
    "metadata" as message.metadata Let json_string be serialize_to_json with data as message_dict
    Return string_to_bytes with text as json_string

Process called "deserialize_ipc_message" that takes data as List[Integer] returns IPCMessage:
    Try:
    Let json_string be bytes_to_string with data as data
    Let message_dict be deserialize_from_json with json as json_string Return IPCMessage with:
    message_id as message_dict["message_id"]
    message_type as message_dict["message_type"]
    priority as message_dict["priority"]
    sender_id as message_dict["sender_id"]
    recipient_id as message_dict["recipient_id"]
    payload as message_dict["payload"]
    payload_size as length of data
    timestamp as message_dict["timestamp"]
    expiration_time as 0.0
    sequence_number as message_dict["sequence_number"]
    acknowledgment_required as false
    encryption_enabled as false
    compression_enabled as false
    checksum as message_dict["checksum"]
    metadata as message_dict["metadata"]
    Catch error:
    Return empty

Note: Utility Functions for IPC Operations
Process called "generate_unique_id" returns String:
    Return generate_uuid

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Return get_system_time_microseconds divided by 1000000.0

Process called "get_current_process_id" returns String:
    Return get_process_id_string

Process called "get_next_sequence_number" returns Integer:
    Let counter be get_global_sequence_counter
    Set counter to counter 1
    Return counter

Process called "calculate_payload_size" that takes payload as Any returns Integer:
    Let serialized be serialize_to_json with data as payload
    Return length of serialized

Process called "calculate_message_checksum" that takes payload as Any returns String:
    Let serialized be serialize_to_json with data as payload
    Let data_bytes be string_to_bytes with text as serialized
    Return calculate_sha256_hash with data as data_bytes

Process called "update_pipe_stats" that takes pipe as Pipe and operation as String and bytes as Integer:
    If "stats" is not in pipe.metadata:
    Set pipe.metadata["stats"] to dictionary containing Let stats be pipe.metadata["stats"]
    Let key be operation followed by "_bytes"
    If key is not in stats:
    Set stats[key] to 0 Set stats[key] to stats[key] bytes
    Set stats["last_operation"] to operation
    Set stats["last_update"] to get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_channel_stats" returns ChannelStats:
    Return ChannelStats with:
    messages_sent as 0
    messages_received as 0
    bytes_sent as 0
    bytes_received as 0
    errors as 0
    average_latency as 0.0
    max_latency as 0.0
    min_latency as 0.0
    throughput_mbps as 0.0
    last_updated as get_current_timestamp
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "min" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
    Return a
    Else:
    Return b

Process called "max" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
    Return a
    Else:
    Return b